[b]Vein: Reversal Zones[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

Draws horizontal S/R zones at price levels where ATR-confirmed, quality-graded reversals occurred historically. Zones are derived from the same forward-evaluation logic as the Vein Reversal Labeler: a bar is classified as a reversal only if price moved the required ATR multiple in the right direction within the evaluation window without first hitting the adverse limit.

A live signal engine monitors five configurable triggers and fires when a trigger coincides with price being near one of those validated zones.

[b]Zones[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Support zones[/b] — span [low → close] of confirmed bull reversal bars: the range price dipped into and recovered from
[*][b]Resistance zones[/b] — span [close → high] of confirmed bear reversal bars: the range price pushed into and rejected from
[*]Strong reversals (label +2 / −2) and weak reversals (label +1 / −1) are shown in distinct styles
[*]Only the nearest N zones within a configurable ATR range are displayed; the rest are stored but hidden
[*]Nearby zones of the same direction merge automatically; each zone carries a touch counter
[*]Zones are optionally deleted when price closes fully through them
[/list]

[b]Signal Triggers[/b]

Five triggers are independently toggleable:
[list]
[*][b]WaveTrend Cross[/b] — WT1 crosses WT2 in oversold (long) or overbought (short) territory
[*][b]RSI Reclaim[/b] — RSI crosses back above the OS level (long) or back below the OB level (short)
[*][b]Supertrend Flip[/b] — Supertrend direction changes bullish (long) or bearish (short)
[*][b]Candle Sweep[/b] — price violates a recent swing extreme and closes back inside (liquidity grab)
[*][b]MA / Momentum[/b] — close crosses a configurable MA (EMA / RMA / SMA / WMA / HMA / JMA, default RMA) with MACD histogram confirming direction
[/list]

[b]Signal Modes[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Known Zones[/b] (default) — signal fires only when price is within the proximity threshold of an existing zone
[*][b]Candidates[/b] — signal fires on trigger alone, without requiring zone proximity
[*][b]Both[/b] — fires in both cases; solid arrow (▲/▼) marks zone-confluent signals, outline arrow (△/▽) marks candidates
[/list]

[b]Trigger Requirement[/b]

Set to [b]Any[/b] (one enabled trigger is enough) or [b]2+[/b] (at least two must fire simultaneously) to control signal sensitivity.

[b]Cooldown[/b]

A configurable bar cooldown per direction prevents signal clusters after a valid entry.


